Utility to do base64 encoding/decoding

Usage:

base64 [file]
  Writes base64 encoding of given file to stdout.
  If no file given then stdin is used.

base64 -d [file]
  Writes base64 decoding of given file to stdout.
  If no file given then stdin is used.

Options:
  -w<num>  when encoding, wrap after given number of columns
  -i       when decoding, ignore garbage
  -h       show help and exit
  -v       show version and exit

ChangeLog:
[2013-02-16] Handle newlines, support -i -w
[2012-10-28] Port to libcore 3.0
[2012-01-23] Port to libcore 2.0
